<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-07-0674 </DOCNO><TEXT>A chain-hauled conveyor belt comprises a conveyor belt resting on rollers,a link chain attached to the belt, a drive unit and conveyor belt returningapparatus. The conveyor belt is characterised in that the drive consistsof a motor, a reducing gear with a series of drive shafts and a seriesof pinions which engage with racks which in turn engage the belt chainto drive same, the belt and chain passing over a return drum with a centralgroove to accommodate the chain. The rack comprises a series of linksjoined by pins. The series of pinions are positioned in pairs on oppositesides of the belt chain. A plurality of drive units may be provided alongthe conveyor length.</TEXT></DOC>